.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-SYNC 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 0.5.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-sync \- two-way sync with an external provider
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue sync
.IR github: <owner> / <repo>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Perform a two-way synchronization with an external issue tracker.
This is a convenience wrapper that runs
.BR "git issue import" (1)
followed by
.BR "git issue export" (1)
against the same provider.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-state " " <state>
Filter for the import phase:
.BR open " (default), " closed ", " all .
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would happen without making changes (passed to both
import and export).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Sync with GitHub:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue sync github:owner/repo
.fi
.RE
.PP
Dry-run to preview changes:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue sync github:owner/repo --dry-run --state all
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-import (1),
.BR git\-issue\-export (1)
